snippet.textDisplay: As a huge admirer of Leed United (not a fan/supporter), I desperately want this Yorkshire giant to return to where they rightly belong (premier league). However, I am afraid that with this style of football or sort of defending, it might end in tears again that Leeds may miss out again on a promotion like they did last year and the year before. You cannot gain promotion playing - if you score one we would score two types of football after going two goals up away from home. It is enjoyable to watch for neutrals like myself but in reality, it would be detrimental to Leeds promotion aspirations in the long term. I very much doubt if Mr 'eccentric' Bielsa is the right guy to take Leeds into their promised land quest. I still would wish them well and hope that they make it to the finish line this term.

snippet.textDisplay:
Unbelievable!
I’m in New Zealand and I was up just before 6am to get ready for work.
I turned on my iPad, which is a bit old now and a bit slow, and checked the Leeds result, they were 3-2 up with under 8 minutes to go.
I checked the West Bromwich result and then went to check the table which was being updated Live.
Again, the old iPad is a bit slow...
Well, I checked the table and we were still second and I thought that’s a bit odd so went back and checked the score... now it read 3-3.

I went back to the Table and now it had Leeds back on top, rechecked the result and now it was 4-3!

And so it went... I thought at one point maybe I was still asleep and dreaming...

To cut a long story very short... I have never seen a score and a live table change so much in the last few minutes of a football match.
To go from 3-2 up then 3-3, 4-3, 4-4, 5-4 was just unbelievable.

Come on Leeds, you can do it. (I think I’ve aged 10 years today!)

I’m in New Zealand and I was up just before 6am to get ready for work.
I turned on my iPad, which is a bit old now and a bit slow, and checked the Leeds result, they were 3-2 up with under 8 minutes to go.
I checked the West Bromwich result and then went to check the table which was being updated Live.
Again, the old iPad is a bit slow...
Well, I checked the table and we were still second and I thought that’s a bit odd so went back and checked the score... now it read 3-3.

I went back to the Table and now it had Leeds back on top, rechecked the result and now it was 4-3!

And so it went... I thought at one point maybe I was still asleep and dreaming...

To cut a long story very short... I have never seen a score and a live table change so much in the last few minutes of a football match.
To go from 3-2 up then 3-3, 4-3, 4-4, 5-4 was just unbelievable.

Come on Leeds, you can do it. (I think I’ve aged 10 years today!)
